","Heroldstone,Pembroke,Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","<Of Rathcoffy, Kildare, Ireland>":"Rathcoffey, County Kildare, Ierland"},"en":{"1330–1378":"1330–1378","1326–Female":"1326–Deceased","1340–Female":"1340–Deceased","1359–Female":"1359–Deceased","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1305–1349":"1305–1349","1305–1378":"1305–1378","1327":"1327","1349":"1349","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","1378":"1378","about 1359":"about 1359","1330":"1330","13 January 1349":"13 January 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1428":"1428","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Rhoscrowther, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Rhoscrowther, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Trabzon, Ortahisar, Trabzon, Turkey":"Trabzon, Ortahisar, Trabzon, Türkiye","Heroldstone,Pembroke,Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom","<Of Rathcoffy, Kildare, Ireland>":"Rathcoffey, County Kildare, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Perrot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Gilles, Veronique.","French: from a pet form of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perrotte  .","Breton: from a French-influenced pet form (see 1 above) of the personal name <i>Per</i>, Breton form of   Peter  . Compare   Perro  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Perrotte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Damien, Henri.","Altered form of French   Perrot   or   Perrault  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>.","French: from the feminine form of   Perrot  ."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter Perrot was born in 1330, in Rhoscrowther, Pembrokeshire, Wales, his father, John Perrot, was 25 and his mother, Jane Joyce, was 25. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Alice Harrold. He died in 1378, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1330–1378":"1330–1378","1326–Female":"1326–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1359–Female":"1359–Surnud","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1305–1349":"1305–1349","1305–1378":"1305–1378","1327":"1327","1349":"1349","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1326":"1326","1378":"1378","about 1359":"umbes 1359","1330":"1330","13 January 1349":"13. jaanuar 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1428":"1428","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","Rhoscrowther, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Rhoscrowther, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Trabzon, Ortahisar, Trabzon, Turkey":"Trabzon, Ortahisar, Trabzon, Türgi","Heroldstone,Pembroke,Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom"